Five friends from Adamawa State have been killed in a ghastly car accident while on their way to Kaduna State. According to reports, the men were burnt beyond recognition in the crash which occurred on Saturday.  An aide to Ahmadu Fintiri, Adamawa State Governor, Miracle Musa, made this known in a post via his Facebook account on Sunday. He wrote on Facebook: “Five Adamawa boys, all perished, burnt beyond recognition. On their way to Kaduna to convey 'Kayan tambaya' for their friend’s engagement. Three are from Bekaji while the other two were from Karewa GRA.” Two of the men have been so far identified as Saddam Aje Shinguboi and Mwaniya Japhet Gajere. The three others had not been identified as at the time of filing this report. Meanwhile, the Senator representing Adamawa North, Ishaku Abbo, in a post via his social media account condoled with the families, friends and well-wishers of the deceased over their death.